    <etym xml:lang="ru">Близкие соответствия в кавказских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>galawani</w><gloss><q>крепкая, большая стена</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Саба"/><biblScope>193</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sva"><lang/><w>galwän</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
                ><lang/><w>a-galwan, a-galawan</w><gloss><q>ограда</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Марр._Абх."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>galan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
                ><lang/><w>ǧalan</w><gloss><q>крепостная стена</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_СМК"/><biblScope>XXIX 28</biblScope></bibl>). Слово имеет
        %bперсидский%b облик: во второй части — %ivān%i из <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>pān</w><gloss><q>ограждение</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>защита</q></gloss></mentioned>, (как в %igirēvan%i
        ‘воротник’, %ianguštvān%i ‘наперсток’, %ipuštvān%i ‘опора’, ‘защита’ и др.); первая часть
        %igala%i, может быть, из <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kala
                    (qala)</w><gloss><q>крепость</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>укрепленное поселение</q></gloss></mentioned>, (относительно
        последнего слова см.: <bibl><biblScope>Encyclopédie de l’Islam II 710</biblScope></bibl>). В
        осетинский слово вошло, всего вероятнее, из соседних кавказских языков.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Close correspondences in Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>galawani</w><gloss><q>firm, big wall</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Саба"/><biblScope>193</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>galwän</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/><w>a-galwan,
                a-galawan</w><gloss><q>fence</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Марр._Абх."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>galan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
                ><lang/><w>ǧalan</w><gloss><q>pinion wall</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_СМК"/><biblScope>XXIX 28</biblScope></bibl>). The word has %bPersian%b
        look: in the second part there is %ivān%i from <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>pān</w><gloss><q>fence</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>defence</q></gloss></mentioned>, (as in %igirēvan%i
        ‘collar’, %ianguštvān%i ‘thimble’, %ipuštvān%i ‘support’, ‘defence’ etc.); the first part
        %igala%i may be from <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>kala
                    (qala)</w><gloss><q>fortress</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>fortified settlement</q></gloss></mentioned>, (as for the last
        word, see: <bibl><biblScope>Encyclopédie de l’Islam II 710</biblScope></bibl>). Most likely,
        the word entered Ossetic from neighbouring Caucasian languages.%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
